import React from 'react';
import { Card, ListGroup, Button } from 'react-bootstrap'
const custom_style = { width: '45%', borderRadius: "10px", marginLeft: "0" };

function JobCardComponent(data) {
    return (

        <
        div className = "JobsCardComponent" >
        <
        Card style = {
            { width: '100%', borderRadius: "10px" } } >
        <
        div className = "flexBox_column_joined" >
        <
        Card.Body style = {
            { width: '30%' } } >
        <
        Card.Img variant = "top"
        style = { custom_style }
        src = { data.jobImageUrl }
        /> <
        Card.Title > { data.JobCompanyName } < /Card.Title> <
        /Card.Body> <
        ListGroup className = "list-group-flush"
        style = {
            { width: '70%' } } >
        <
        div className = "flexBox_column_joined" >
        <
        p > Designation: < /p> <
        p > { data.jobDesignation } < /p> <
        /div> <
        div className = "flexBox_column_joined" >
        <
        p > Expected Salary: < /p> <
        p > { data.jobSalary } < /p> <
        /div> <
        div className = "flexBox_column_joined" >
        <
        p > Location: < /p> <
        p > { data.jobLocation } < /p> <
        /div>

        <
        div className = "flexBox_column_joined" >
        <
        p > Expiry Date: < /p> <
        p > { data.jobExpireDate } < /p> <
        /div> <
        div className = "flexBox_column_joined" >
        <
        p > Level: < /p> <
        p > { data.jobLevel } < /p> <
        /div>

        <
        Button variant = "primary"
        style = {
            { marginTop: "20px" } } > Apply Now < /Button> <
        /ListGroup> <
        /div>


        <
        /Card> <
        /div>
    )
}

export default JobCardComponent;
